    "body": "<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Gaurav has a box of infinte capacity containing infinite \"sandwiches\". His friend has N boxes, each numbered as 1,2,3....N, all of capacity N each. His task is to distribute the items from the infinite box into these N boxes such that no 2 boxes have the same number of items and every box is filled, i.e. non empty. <br>Also, an even numbered box cannot have even number of \"sandwiches\", and an odd numbered box cannot have odd number of \"sandwiches\". <br>\nHelp him find the total number of \"sandwiches\" together in all after the distribution.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>First line contains an integer <b>T</b> denoting number of test cases.<br>\nEach test case contains one line denoting number of boxes, <b>N</b>.<br>\n<b>N</b> is guaranteed an even number.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Output the total number of \"sandwiches\" after the required distribution.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>10</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>10^9</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n1\n4<br>\n<b>Output:</b>\n10\n</pre>",
